Summary Profile: 
An independent consultant that has been in the SAP Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) industry for almost 20 years designing, configuring, integrating and developing end-to-end business solutions and processes to optimize productivity, reduce operating cost and increase customer satisfaction in Provincial and Federal Government Departments and Agencies, Municipal, Energy, Oil and Gas, Transportation and Consumer Packaged Goods industry sectors. 

Core Accomplishment: 
•	As a solution architect, project manager and team lead consultant, I analyzed, designed and configured the latest SAP products and third party technologies to address business requirements for Procure-to-Pay and Process-to-Order solutions that resulted in the successful execution of assorted large and medium scale projects. 
•	Completed 10+ full cycle SAP implementations in the capability of a Consultant, Lead Consultant, Project Manager and Solution Architect.  
•	Provide guidance positioning clients on the appropriate SAP solutions and technologies to enable organizations meets their critical business requirements. 
•	Established relationships with senior leaders in providing recommendations on SAP’s solutions and offerings to improve and optimize system and business process execution. 
•	Work hand-in-hand with development team Architect on best business practice approach for system enhancements. 
•	Took leadership and ownership to achieve project scope timelines, objectives and deliverables that resulted in a client’s high level of satisfactions. 
•	Designed and implemented project procedures and governance that effectively streamlined business processes and system changes tractability. Summary Profile: 
